item.description:
For me, it doesn&rsquo;t feel nice to use touchpad buttons to click something, i&rsquo;m prefer use touchpad area to click.
you need to install libinput because synaptics ( based on Arch Wiki ) is in maintenance mode and is no longer updated. {% highlight shell %} $ sudo pacman -S libinput xf86-input-libinput {% endhighlight %}
add 30-touchpad.conf to /etc/X11/xorg.conf.d/: {% highlight shell %} $ sudo vim /etc/X11/xorg.conf.d/30-touchpad.conf {% endhighlight %}
